message.content:
Analysis of the Target Structure:

• Total Blocks and Layers  
  – There are five total blocks used.  
  – You can view them as forming three “levels”:  
    1) Bottom horizontal yellow beam  
    2) Two tall green pillars plus a second horizontal yellow beam resting on them  
    3) A single red triangular “roof” block perched on top  

• Spatial Arrangement  
  – The bottom yellow beam lies flat.  
  – Two green pillars stand vertically on this beam, spaced apart at left and right.  
  – Another yellow beam spans across the tops of the two green pillars.  
  – A red triangular prism (roof‐shaped block) sits centered on that upper beam.  

Selecting the Correct Dictionary Blocks:

1) Green Vertical Columns:  
   – Use block index 3 (the tall green vertical prism).  
   – Needed twice (one for each pillar).  

2) Yellow Horizontal Beams (top and bottom):  
   – Use block index 4 (long yellow rectangular block lying horizontally left‐to‐right).  
   – Needed twice (for the bottom and top beams).  

3) Red Triangular “Roof”:  
   – Use block index 10 (red wedge oriented so that its triangular face is “front‐to‐back,” matching the roof slope).  
   – Needed once.  

Assembly Order (JSON‐like format):

{
  Step1: Move block with index 4,
  Step2: Move block with index 3,
  Step3: Move block with index 3,
  Step4: Move block with index 4,
  Step5: Move block with index 10
}
